column2: The University of California, Santa Barbara (a public research school) is #5 in Top Public Schools in the nation according to U.S. News & World Report. It is one of the 10 campuses of the University of California system.
The Griffith Observatory is a facility in Los Angeles, California, sitting on the south-facing slope of Mount Hollywood in Los Angeles' Griffith Park.
Two hills in the "City by the Bay" where people gather to see the incredible views of San Francisco.
A national forest in Northern California next to Yosemite National Park.
A beach in Isla Vista where many UCSB students and local residents go to surf, watch the sunset, and enjoy time with friends!

Hollywood is a neighborhood in the central region of Los Angeles, California, notable as the home of the U.S. film industry, including several of its historic studios. Its name has come to be a shorthand reference for the industry and the people associated with it.
